+{"id":"frankenpandas-ii9u","title":"fd90.59: umbrella must forward fp-runtime asupersync and fp-frame tracing features","description":"Continuation of fd90.58: the frankenpandas umbrella now forwards fp-io sql-* features but other crates have feature flags that umbrella users still cannot enable. fp-runtime exposes asupersync (off by default - depends on asupersync crate). fp-frame exposes tracing (off by default - emits tracing spans on hot paths). fp-conformance already forwards asupersync. The umbrella should expose these as features users can opt into. Add to umbrella Cargo.toml: tracing = fp-frame/tracing. asupersync = fp-runtime/asupersync. Both default-off (matches the underlying crate defaults). No other features need adding. Verify both profiles compile.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"cc-pandas-2","created_at":"2026-04-26T05:23:29.742116450Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T05:26:38.213615519Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T05:26:38.211076975Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["build","fd90","review"]}
